I was supposed to be working, but I got distracted and made these. Har. Pics of the Day from the Beeb. My favorite service offering photos of the day is the BBC, as the images are from all over the world and generally fascinating. First set are from a photo from the Bali royal cremation ceremony. Credit for original image is to the AP.

This last photo is of a duck and her duckling in the Spree River in Berlin, Germany, with a giant-ass (in duck terms) hunk of pita. Credit for the original image goes to AFP. And, yes, there's an intentional joke within the LOLDUK joke.
1.   2.
And then there's the reason why I started making icons today instead of working on the stuff I get paid to do, which is this part of a photo taken by Beverly Joubet for the National Geographic Society and is one of the images which shuffles through my desktop. (There's only the one because, by the time I started making this, I was really feeling guilty for futzing around with pictures instead of doing work.)
Look at that! Two icon posts within the same month!

I should have been working. Instead, I was making these. If they'd just keep that damned database up and running like it's supposed to, I wouldn't have time to be distracted by thoughts of LOLCATS versions of National Geographic photographs. Random icons, with tiger. There's comedianne Maria Bamford (6), LOLTIGER! (1-5; photograph by Joel Sartore for the National Geographic Society; LOLness by my weird brain), detail from Madame de Pompadour by Henri Matisse (7 & 8), something Welsh (dragon from the flag), and that's it for now.

Was watching old movies on TCM, then watched Lost and This American Life off the DVR. Then, even though I was really freaking tired and sick, I stayed up and watched the [adult swim] anime line-up on the DVR and made the following from screencaps created by . I am a moron. I'm also feeling like warmed-over cat sick. Whee! Peter Pan, the very good 2005 film version. I have never forgiven my mother for having told me I couldn't be Wendy in the summer production of the musical in Maryland when I was 12 going on 13. It was my first-ever audition and I totally nailed it. I could not understand why she wouldn't let me be Wendy, the freakin' lead. She denies this ever happened, but my friend at the time, who auditioned with me and barely made the chorus, remembers very well, as she was completely pissed that I got the part and gloated the rest of the time I knew her over being in the show when I wasn't. Arg. Anyway, my icons based on the very good movie.

...still sucking. Yeah, yeah, Mom. Negativity is a self-fulfilling prophecy. Blah blah blah. Anyway, I wandered over to 's icons site to see what I could see, and I found she'd screencapped a bunch of interesting images, which I then proceeded to turn into icons. Whoops. Go get 's icons. They're way better. The Chronicles of Narnia: The Lion, The Witch, and The Wardrobe the movie, which I liked. I had a bookgeek crush on Peter when I was a kid, so I was pleased to see they cast someone I would have totally crushed on when I was that age. I used to hate Lucy. Now I love her. I thought the girl who played her was perfect, if not how I imagined her to look. Susan is and always will be a bitch. I'll never forgive her for saying Narnia was just pretend. Grr! Edmund, I'm happy to say, stops being a whiny bastard by the second book. I hope they get Lucy and Edmund back for the second film.

Aw, crap. In the fansubs I watched, the names were rather funky. Sometimes the translation from European-ish names into kana into Engrish made for bizarre names. But, you know, that's anime. But now I'm all confused. The main characters' names I'm sure of, but the secondary and tertiary are... well, I've no idea. For instance, is it supposed to be Havok or Havoc? Help?


[EDIT 8/18: Fuck. Okay. I went to the official FMA American website. It's Havoc. Now I have to change the damned icons. Arg. You have no idea how hard that is to do in PowerPoint, dammit. This is what I get from giving credence to fansubbers.]

Finally finished watching FMA. Spent a lot of time screencapping the last few episodes. I don't know why, seeing as there's an entire community here on LJ dedicated to FMA screencaps. I guess I'm just a moron that way. Fullmetal Alchemist, set 2, in which there are a lot of spoilers for those who haven't watched the entire series. (Are there any of you left, or was I the last one?) Wow. This is a lot of icons. And a couple of them are actually rather good. Le yay.

I haven't posted any of my icons anywhere but here (and a few at my other LJ, which I've since moved to here).

I know these aren't exactly the greatest graphics in 100x100 format ever, but... Um... Should I post them somewhere? If so, where?

Other people scare me. Even other people I never see. I guess I'll never stop being that debilitatingly shy ten year old.

My sister and her son are flying back to Paris later today. I'm staying up to record this movie about blues which I'd DVRed for my brother-in-law but forgot to transfer to a DVD. Why? Because I'm an idiot. As I'm not really all that interested in the history of juke joints in Mississippi, I decided to make icons while waiting for the film to end. (Which it did, about a minute and a half after I ran out of space on the DVD. Dammit.) I screencapped a couple of mid-series Fullmetal Alchemist episodes and used some MS Clip Art photos. Tra la, tra la. It's very late indeed. Fullmetal Alchemist. My very first crappy FMA icons. Whee!

Nature, in all of its MS Clip Art glory. Some summer-ish themes, some fall, some winter. I like fall and winter best, as I don't do well in warm weather. Something about the brisk fall air in late September really gets my brain going. And I love snow. One of the most beautiful sights in this world is powder snow glittering in the light of a full moon.

Had the most bizzare allergic reaction to whatever was in the air today. Sure, yeah, the sinuses were in pain, but my throat swelled up and nearly closed up. It's still very sore. The allergy medicine I took did nothing to alleviate the symptoms, of course, but it has made me slightly trippy, which may explain some of the icons behind the cut. There's Howl's Moving Castle, but there's also Batman Begins, NYC subway, and ... well, pervy-slashy InuYasha icons. The last are the fault of , who sent me a link to the cell image and made a glancing reference to its potential for slashy-slashy misinterpretation. (Yeah, I know. The quote's off. What do you want. I only saw the movie once.) Howl's Moving Castle, Set 5

I'm an HP otaku. ... Okay, so, like, I'm a fan. Hey, I'm one of the few Americans who knew about Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone before it was optioned by Scholastic. I've a freakin' first edition of the American edition (which was erroneously titled, hence my purchase of only UK editions starting with Chamber of Secrets ...thank goodness Amazon.co.uk'd started up). Still, um, yeah. I don't have an encyclopedic memory of every last detail. Anyway, here's my attempt to be fannish with the HP. First with the champion support. Layout didn't work out as well on the non-Hogwarts champions, but-- you-- screw them! They're not Hogwarts! (Hogwarts, Hogwarts, Hoggy-warty Hogwarts.) Also, I support Potter, so, um, which explains why his is better than Cedric's. Right. There. *cough* Anyway, the champion photos/names are from the champion support kits from the official Goblet of Fire movie site. I can't for the life of me remember where I got the Griffindor and Hufflepuff seals. Durmstrang and Beauxbatons were snagged from apparently defunct sites (though it may be that they were just not working when I was searching Google).

This is not a f'locked journal, unlike my journal journal, which is f'locky in all sorts of ways. This is a journal where I shall place my pathetic attempts at iconage, among other types of web-based imagery. I shall try to credit image sources, as well as text sources, as best I can. This means I'll credit the original composer/performer, rather than the person who happens to be singing it now. I'll try to credit the artist, the person who did the screencap, all that jazz. If I don't know or don't remember, I will say so. In that case, please let me know if you know whose work it was. I currently have no access to decent software. I work on an ancient PC with Roxio, which is teh suck (its code is pastede on yay), and my PowerBook with PowerPoint. I'm hoping to improve over time in spite of the limitations of my software and my poor native talent. The icons will be All Sorts: anime, manga, old movies, text quotes, other people's art (as I cannot draw myself, I must snag and crop others' works and squish them into mean little boxes), new movies, television shows, the Yankees, cats, trees, flowers, Coldplay, France, Japan, New England, alcohol, food, books, Monty Python, or whatever else crops up in my tiny mind and can be put into a 100x100 pixel icon. I will take requests, but wonder at your making them, as there are infinitely superior icon-makers out there in LJ and the 'Web. RULES: I shall take constructive criticism, and, in fact, welcome it, as I desperately need it. I will delete the obnoxious, the annoying, and, possibly, those who write in attrocious English (unless I'm given a VERY good excuse, such as you're a fourteen year old Japanese kid and new to the language, or summat like). Typos are a given, though. Everyone goes on LJ at, like, three in the morning. Exhaustion is not conducive to perfect typing. I would like comments in general, but I really must insist upon crediting. Crediting should mean that when someone slides their mouse over your icon, they read not only your shortcut name for the icon but the name of the user who made it. It's what I do with other user's icons which I have taken. It's what I expect of everyone else. Please just put sugarkat_icons in the keywords when you add the icon. ABSOLUTELY NO HOTLINKING. That will lead to me f'locking this journal and you getting publicly humiliated. Trust me on this. LJ allows you to upload pictures from your harddrive when setting up your icons. There is no reason for hotlinking, except extreme laziness and/or stupidity. Don't hotlink, or the entire world will know you are brain damaged in a manner only possible through inbreeding (and I will henceforth assume your sister/brother and your wife/husband are one and the same person). Need a photo account in which to store your icons? Try Photobucket. (They're free!) I must also insist that you please not change the images without permission. If you think you can make it better, let me know. I'll probably agree wholeheartedly and say all right, but please don't be so rude as to assume that I will. Honestly, the image sources are commonly found, so I can't image you won't be able to find the original and do what you will. No rudeness. Yes, that's vague, but I think you should know. Your mother taught you better. Even poor, orphaned and abused Harry Potter knows better than that. I'll delete when you've violated this rule. Think of it as the nun rapping your knuckles for misbehavior during Sunday School. (Frickin' nuns.) If you are a frequent abuser of this rule, I'll simply set this journal into friends-only mode. Yes, I'm that stubborn. (Rhymes with witch!) Swearing and profanity are permitted, encouraged even, but racist, sexist, homophobic, etc., comments are not. Please do not make assumptions about me or those who might come to this journal and what we may or may not find amusing/offensive. Well, just assume that this is like a new office/classroom, where you have to be on, ah, your better behavior. Jokes and humor are very much welcome. Just please don't be an asshole about it. Try wit, darling. Finally, please, please post if you take any of the icons posted in this journal. I will be terrifically surprised to find anyone does and I want to be able to thank those who do. This isn't really a rule, just a request. Thank you!
